iv been reflecting alot lately. realizing how lucky i am to have the life i do. i really havent taken the time to appreciate everything and everyone the way i should.

thank you to my family for putting up with me. thankyou mom for still hiding my easter basket even though i am 'too old' to still be doing it. thank you dad for always making me laugh. and sharing the bathroom with me in the morning while i growl at you for waking me up. thank you teddy for being cute and for not being one of those punkass kids that think theyre all that. in other words thank you for being the cutest nerd 7th grader ever, i dont know what id do if i didnt have someone to laugh at fart jokes with me. last but not least thankyou margo for being my absolute best friend. i know so many sisters out there who cant even be in the same room without fighting. thankyou for sharing clothes and makeup etc because even if i act pissed, i like having a sister to be girly with.

thankyou jordan for sitting with me at skiclub. tbs will always be there for us even if they are on trl now. thanks for eating bad popcorn with me and summersaulting around my house. thanks for being 'real' and having heart to heart convos about random things on my mind... for always being there for me and THANKS FOR US NEVER FIGHTING EVER. its still going.

thankyou grace for being the weirdest person i know. thanks for putting chocolate pudding in my hair. thanks for having a dog named owen who will never leave me alone ever. thanks for convincing mrs gugino sandy got papsmears weekly. thanks for coming with me to the cheapest stores in the world because im poor. and for having a digital camera that is addictive.

thankyou alex for being the cutest boy ever. i cant even tell you how much you mean to me. thanks for liking fievo goes west as much as me. thanks for being a good pillow every once in a while. thanks for making everyone jealous with me. for leaving cute notes on my board. for having the funniest voicemail ever. for promising things. for always being there for me and listening to my dumb stories.  for letting me love you.

thankyou alex hillery for hating school with me. and creating coffee music in reading and worksheets. for cheating on everything possible with me and being sweet about it.

thank you rich for listening to all my problems and being so supportive throughout everything. thanks for having a hottub too :)

thankyou kevin for being the nicest kid ever and putting up with me. thanks for making me laugh in skiclub and thanks for liking my cd mixes because i like making them alot.

thanks taylor for being sooooo goofy and never giving me a moment to breath. thanks for being a slut too.

thankyou kyle for being my 'brother'. thanks for giving me advice and just being a friend when i needed one. thanks for sneaking me in your car to go places and letting me pick the music.

thankyou laura greenway for sneaking a chalupa into the movies. it gets no better than that.

thankyou linzi for being soooo nice and being my soulmate.

thankyou dave for being sucha good model

thankyou yankeedoodle for being so nickname-able. and for being on our volleyball team once in a while.

thankyou amanda for being friends with me since kindergarden. thanks for letting your dog fart on me alot. thanks for meeting boys in florida with me. thanks for sleeping in bikinis and eating cookies for breakfast.

thankyou emjo for being crazy and playing games in the reflection off the door in math. thanks for tickling me and for causing getman to look at me weird. thanks for falling on your face at the dance and making me laugh.

thankyou **** ****** for being conceited and giving me and alex something new to compain about

thankyou becky for being hilarious in english and for having pink spandex

thankyou mrs martin for being the most sarcastic person i know. and for giving us tasks like its nobodys business. there. sarcasm for a sarcastic person.

thankyou katie for writing chris the letter about him looking like a FAS kid. for doing what everyone wanted to do but didnt have the guts to.

thankyou sean for making retarded faces in math and not realizing you look likea moron. thanks for making me laugh likea fool because your faces kick ass

theres so many more people id love to thank but for now. thankyou bed for being really comfortable and letting me sleep curled up ina ball. <33

i love you all.

last night. was amazing. around 3 me n jor went to grace's, made popcorn and watched donnie darko. got to the icon around 6 when the doors were supposed to open, waited in the car til the line started to move... doors didnt open til way later and by the time a thorn for every heart finally started playin it was 715ish. we found a good spot on the side of the stage where we could all see from. hellogoodbye was awesome. soooo cute. grace got tons of pics of them, ill post as soon as she send them to me. punchline was alrite. im getting sick of them, iv seen them like 4 times already damnit, theyre everywhere. thennnnn for my favoriteeeeeee. HIDDEN IN PLAIN VIEW. they were soooooo good. while we were still standing by the stage this kid came up and stood by the wall next to me. so im like 'jor check this kid out' and she told grace. and i guess she knew him or something? haha. so us sneaky kids took a pic of 'me' to get him in the background. (like 3 times) after the 2nd time he totally knew what we were doing and turned around and smiled for it haha. and when we went to go sit down we shared a seat? yep... we're cool. katelyn was off talking to one of the guys in the band and got his number. he was 27, shes 17. niiiiiiiiice haha. he was cute tho. while we we leaving rob from hipv signed a poster for me and i got a pic with him. he looks gay haha. i bought a tshirt, track jacket and cd... got some free posters too.

so the whole night i was lookin for al... couldnt find him :(... when we were walking out i felt someone grab my side and he was there. i cant believe we were there the whole night and didnt see each other. fucking sucks.

but overall this was the best concert iv been to in a looong time. so amazing. hipv played 20 below last and all the other bands went on stage and stuff, kids were goin nuts crowd surfing and throwing water bottles around..  it was just like 'wow this is awesome' i cant even explain it.... sooooooo good!!! <333
